limit.label: Series limit
limit.description: Limits the number of series that get displayed. A joined subquery (or an extra phase where subqueries are not supported) is applied to limit the number of series that get fetched and rendered. This feature is useful when grouping by high cardinality column(s) though does increase the query complexity and cost.

timeseries_limit_metric.label: Sort by
timeseries_limit_metric.description: This metric is used to define row selection criteria (how the rows are sorted) if a series or row limit is present. If not defined, it reverts to the first metric (where appropriate).

order_desc.description: If enabled, this control sorts the results/values descending, otherwise it sorts the results ascending.

rolling_type.label: Rolling function
rolling_type.description: Defines a rolling window function to apply, works along with the [Periods] text box

rolling_periods.label: Periods
rolling_periods.description: Defines the size of the rolling window function, relative to the time granularity selected

min_periods.label: Min periods
min_periods.description: The minimum number of rolling periods required to show a value. For instance if you do a cumulative sum on 7 days you may want your "Min Period" to be 7, so that all data points shown are the total of 7 periods. This will hide the "ramp up" taking place over the first 7 periods

time_compare.label: Time shift
time_compare.description: Overlay one or more timeseries from a relative time period. Expects relative time deltas in natural language (example:  24 hours, 7 days, 52 weeks, 365 days). Free text is supported.

comparison_type.label: Calculation type
comparison_type.description: How to display time shifts: as individual lines; as the difference between the main time series and each time shift; as the percentage change; or as the ratio between series and time shifts.

forecastPeriods.label: Forecast periods
forecastPeriods.description: How many periods into the future do we want to predict

forecastInterval.label: Confidence interval
forecastInterval.description: Width of the confidence interval. Should be between 0 and 1

forecastSeasonalityYearly.label: Yearly seasonality
forecastSeasonalityYearly.description: Should yearly seasonality be applied. An integer value will specify Fourier order of seasonality.

forecastSeasonalityWeekly.label: Weekly seasonality
forecastSeasonalityWeekly.description: Should weekly seasonality be applied. An integer value will specify Fourier order of seasonality.

forecastSeasonalityDaily.label: Daily seasonality
forecastSeasonalityDaily.description: Should daily seasonality be applied. An integer value will specify Fourier order of seasonality.
